Remarks . The holotype was chosen as the specimen showing a fully mature shell, with well formed umbilical and apertural features, while the protoconch is eroded. The MNHN and NMNZ paratypes (
Fig. 13
) have the flocculant protoconch sculpture, while also showing the periumbilical lamella as well as a hint of the adumbilical indentation, both unique features in Scissurellidae .
